a is needed in order to program toolpath. In today&rsquo;s manufacturing engineering solid models are primarily used. BobCAD-CAM provides CAD importing as well as full solid modelling functionality so that manufacturers can either import their part models for programming or design them from scratch. This allows shops to easily access CAD parts or make them easier inside of BobCAD-CAM.&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN class="link" style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt; text-decoration: underline;">CAD Design features</SPAN><SPAN style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt; text-decoration: none solid rgb(255, 255, 255);"> include drawing with wireframes, surfaces and solids.</SPAN></P><P style="margin: 0px; border-width: 0px; border-top-style: initial; border-top-color: initial; border-right-style: none; border-right-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-left-style: none; border-left-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-bottom-style: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; line-height: 1.2; font-family: verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt; text-decoration: none solid rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;"><BR></P><P style="margin: 0px; border-width: 0px; border-top-style: initial; border-top-color: initial; border-right-style: none; border-right-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-left-style: none; border-left-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-bottom-style: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; line-height: 1.2; font-family: verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt; text-decoration: none solid rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;"><BR></P><P style="margin: 0px; border-width: 0px; border-top-style: initial; border-top-color: initial; border-right-style: none; border-right-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-left-style: none; border-left-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-bottom-style: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; line-height: 1.2; font-family: verdana, sans-serif; font-size: